COMMAND generate-agents
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents --agent <name> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Generate/update agent-specific workflow proxies and skill outputs. Creates unified proxy files for workflows (cypilot-generate, cypilot-analyze) and the cypilot skill entry point. Supports windsurf, cursor, claude, copilot, openai.
ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --agent  <string>  Agent/IDE key (windsurf, cursor, claude, copilot, openai). Omit to init all supported agents.
  --openai  <boolean>  Shortcut for --agent openai (OpenAI Codex)
  --root  <path>  Project root directory to search from (default: current directory)
  --cypilot-root  <path>  Explicit Cypilot core root (optional override)
  --config  <path>  Path to unified agents config JSON (default: {project-root}/cypilot-agents.json)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Compute changes without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Success (all workflows and skills synced)
  1  Error (invalid args, missing project root, invalid config)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or PARTIAL
  - agent: Agent name
  - workflows: Object with created/updated/renamed/deleted counts
  - skills: Object with created/updated counts and outputs list
  - errors: List of errors if any

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents --agent windsurf
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents --agent claude --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents --agent cursor
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents --openai
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-agents

RELATED:
  - @CLI.init
  - @CLI.info
---

COMMAND self-check
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py self-check [--kit <id>] [--verbose]
DESCRIPTION: Validate example artifacts against their templates (template QA). For each kit package, checks that example.md passes validation against template.md. Ensures templates and examples remain synchronized. (Legacy flag alias: --rule)
WORKFLOW: kits

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <id>  Kit ID to check (if omitted, checks all kits)
  --verbose  <boolean>  Print detailed validation report

EXIT CODES:
  0  All examples pass validation
  1  File system error or no cypilot found
  2  One or more examples failed validation

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - kits_checked: Number of kits checked
  - templates_checked: Number of templates checked
  - results: Per-template results
  - pass_count: Examples that passed
  - fail_count: Examples that failed
  - failures: List of failed examples with error details

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py self-check
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py self-check --kit cypilot-sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py self-check --verbose

RELATED:
  - @CLI.validate-kits
  - @CLI.validate
  - @Workflow.rules
---

COMMAND toc
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py toc <files...> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Generate or update Table of Contents in Markdown files. Parses ATX headings (## … ######) and inserts/updates a TOC between <!-- toc --> and <!-- /toc --> markers. If markers are absent, inserts them after the first H1 heading.

ARGUMENTS:
  files  <path>  required  One or more Markdown file paths to process

OPTIONS:
  --max-level  <number>  [default: 6]  Maximum heading level to include (1-6)
  --indent  <number>  [default: 2]  Indent spaces per nesting level
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would change without writing files
  --skip-validate  <boolean>  Skip post-generation validation

EXIT CODES:
  0  Success
  1  Error (file not found or processing failure)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: OK, PARTIAL, or ERROR
  - files_processed: Number of files processed
  - results: Per-file results with status (UPDATED, UNCHANGED, SKIP, WOULD_UPDATE, ERROR)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py toc architecture/specs/traceability.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py toc --dry-run *.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py toc --max-level 3 README.md DESIGN.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py toc --indent 4 docs/*.md

RELATED:
  - @CLI.validate
  - @CLI.validate-toc
---

COMMAND validate-toc
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-toc <files...> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Validate Table of Contents in Markdown files. Checks that a TOC section exists (either ## Table of Contents heading or <!-- toc --> markers), all TOC anchors point to real headings, all headings are represented in the TOC, and the TOC is not stale.

ARGUMENTS:
  files  <path>  required  One or more Markdown file paths to validate

OPTIONS:
  --max-level  <number>  [default: 6]  Maximum heading level to include (1-6)
  --verbose  <boolean>  Include full error/warning details in output

EXIT CODES:
  0  All files pass validation
  2  One or more files have TOC errors

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, WARN, or FAIL
  - files_validated: Number of files validated
  - error_count: Total errors across all files
  - warning_count: Total warnings across all files
  - results: Per-file results with status (PASS, WARN, FAIL, ERROR) and error/warning details

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-toc architecture/PRD.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-toc --verbose *.md
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py validate-toc --max-level 3 DESIGN.md DECOMPOSITION.md

RELATED:
  - @CLI.toc
  - @CLI.validate
---

COMMAND update
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py update [options]
DESCRIPTION: Update an existing Cypilot installation. Refreshes .core/ from cache, updates kit reference copies, compares blueprint versions (skip same, warn if migration needed), regenerates .gen/ from user blueprints, and ensures config/ scaffold. Never overwrites user config files.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: auto-detect)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files
  --no-interactive  <boolean>  Disable interactive prompts (auto-skip customized markers)
  -y, --yes  <boolean>  Auto-approve all prompts (no interaction)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Update successful
  1  Error (no project root, no cache, etc.)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, WARN, or ABORTED
  - project_root: Resolved project root path
  - cypilot_dir: Resolved Cypilot directory path
  - dry_run: Whether dry-run mode was used
  - actions: Object with core_update, kits, gen_agents, gen_skill, config_* statuses
  - errors: List of errors (if any)
  - warnings: List of warnings (if any)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py update
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py update --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py update --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py update --no-interactive

RELATED:
  - @CLI.init
  - @CLI.kit-migrate
  - @CLI.generate-resources
---

COMMAND spec-coverage
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage [options]
DESCRIPTION: Measure CDSL marker coverage in codebase files. Scans registered codebase paths for @cpt-* traceability markers and reports coverage percentage, granularity score, and per-file details.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --min-coverage  <number>  Minimum coverage percentage (0-100). Exit 2 if below.
  --min-granularity  <number>  Minimum granularity score (0-1). Exit 2 if below.
  --verbose  <boolean>  Include per-file marker details and line ranges
  --output  <path>  Write report to file instead of stdout

EXIT CODES:
  0  Coverage meets thresholds (or no thresholds specified)
  1  Error (no cypilot found, no context)
  2  Coverage below specified threshold

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - summary: Object with total_files, covered_files, coverage_pct, granularity_score
  - files: Per-file coverage details (when --verbose)
  - threshold_failures: List of threshold violations (when thresholds specified)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage --min-coverage 80
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage --verbose
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage --min-coverage 80 --min-granularity 0.5
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py spec-coverage --output coverage-report.json

RELATED:
  - @CLI.validate
  - @CLI.list-ids
---

COMMAND kit install
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install <path> [options]
DESCRIPTION: Install a kit from a local source directory. The source must contain a blueprints/ directory with at least one .md file. Copies blueprints and scripts to reference and config directories, generates resources.

ARGUMENTS:
  path  <path>  required  Path to kit source directory (must contain blueprints/)

OPTIONS:
  --force  <boolean>  Overwrite existing kit
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Installation successful
  1  Error (no project root, no cypilot directory)
  2  Invalid source or kit already installed

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or FAIL
  - action: installed
  - kit: Kit slug
  - version: Kit version
  - files_written: Number of generated files
  - artifact_kinds: List of artifact kinds generated

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install /path/to/my-kit
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install ./kits/sdlc --force
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit install ./kits/sdlc --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.kit-migrate
  - @CLI.generate-resources
---

COMMAND kit update
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update [options]
DESCRIPTION: Update installed kits. Regenerates .gen/ outputs from user blueprints. With --force, overwrites user blueprints with reference copies first.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug to update (default: all)
  --force  <boolean>  Force overwrite user blueprints with reference copies
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Update successful
  2  No kits installed or kit not found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or WARN
  - kits_updated: Number of kits updated
  - results: Per-kit results with action and files_written
  - errors: List of errors (if any)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --force
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit update --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-migrate
  - @CLI.generate-resources
---

COMMAND kit migrate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate [options]
DESCRIPTION: Migrate kit blueprints to latest versions from reference using marker-level three-way merge. Compares reference and user blueprints at the @cpt: marker level, prompts for per-marker accept/decline decisions (updates, insertions, deletions, restorations), and regenerates .gen/ after migration.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug to migrate (default: all)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files
  --no-interactive  <boolean>  Disable interactive prompts (auto-skip customized markers)
  -y, --yes  <boolean>  Auto-approve all prompts (no interaction)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Migration successful (or no migration needed)
  2  No kits installed or kit not found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, FAIL, or ABORTED
  - kits_migrated: Number of kits migrated
  - kits_current: Number of kits already up to date
  - kits_aborted: Number of kits where migration was aborted (if any)
  - results: Per-kit results with blueprint-level details
  - dry_run: Whether dry-run mode was used (if true)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py kit migrate --no-interactive

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND generate-resources
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources [options]
DESCRIPTION: Regenerate kit resources from user blueprints. Processes @cpt: markers in blueprint files to produce templates, rules, checklists, examples, workflows, constraints, and SKILL.md in .gen/kits/{slug}/.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --kit  <string>  Kit slug (default: all)
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Show what would be done without writing files

EXIT CODES:
  0  Generation successful
  2  No kits with blueprints found

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS or WARN
  - kits_processed: Number of kits processed
  - results: Per-kit results with files_written and artifact_kinds
  - errors: List of errors (if any)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources --kit sdlc
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py generate-resources --dry-run

RELATED:
  - @CLI.kit-install
  - @CLI.kit-update
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND migrate
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate [options]
DESCRIPTION: Migrate a v2 Cypilot project to v3. Converts adapter-based layout to blueprint-based three-directory layout (.core/, .gen/, config/), migrates artifacts.json to artifacts.toml, converts AGENTS.md format, installs kits, and validates migration.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: current directory)
  --install-dir  <string>  Cypilot directory relative to project root (default: derived from v2 core path)
  --yes  <boolean>  Skip confirmation prompt
  --dry-run  <boolean>  Detect and show plan only

EXIT CODES:
  0  Migration successful, dry-run complete, or cancelled by user
  1  Error (detection failed, migration failed)

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - status: PASS, DRY_RUN, CANCELLED, or ERROR
  - Migration details (steps performed, files converted, etc.)

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --dry-run
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --yes
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate --project-root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.migrate-config
  - @CLI.init
  - @CLI.update
---

COMMAND migrate-config
SYNOPSIS: python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config [options]
DESCRIPTION: Convert remaining legacy JSON config files to TOML format. Scans for .json config files in the Cypilot directory and converts them to .toml equivalents.

ARGUMENTS:

OPTIONS:
  --project-root  <path>  Project root directory (default: current directory)

EXIT CODES:
  0  Conversion complete

OUTPUT:
  JSON object with:
  - converted_count: Number of files converted
  - skipped_count: Number of files skipped
  - converted: List of converted file paths
  - skipped: List of skipped file paths

EXAMPLE:
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config
  $ python3 scripts/cypilot.py migrate-config --project-root /path/to/project

RELATED:
  - @CLI.migrate
  - @CLI.update
